            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Daring Attempt</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>A negro girl was arrested and committed to jail upon slight suspecion, but
                    we understand there is no positive evience against her. Circumstances, however,
                    satisfy the Superintendant that she is the guilty party...It is believed that
                    the girl's object was to frighten boarders away from the hotel [so] that she
                    might be relieved a portion of her work.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Hanger</ln>
                        <pf>J.M.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Three attempts made on 11/26-28/1857 to burn the American Hotel in
                    Staunton. Bed in the room of J.M. Hanger destroyed on 11/28/1857. Black girl
                    arrested and jailed. Article partially obscured.</summary>
            </div>
